You are working on Pratyaksha (deepfake detection platform).

Core standards:
- Preserve existing architecture and naming conventions.
- Prefer small, readable components with explicit TypeScript types.
- Use existing API helpers in `frontend/lib/api.ts` instead of ad-hoc fetch calls when possible.
- Handle loading, error, and empty states for every async UI.
- Keep UI accessible: keyboard navigable controls, visible focus styles, and ARIA labels for icon-only buttons.

Frontend conventions:
- Next.js App Router pages under `frontend/app`.
- Use client components only when hooks/browser APIs are needed.
- Reuse shared design tokens and Tailwind colors already defined in `app/globals.css`.
- For charts, use Recharts with graceful fallback when data is missing.
- For auth-protected views, rely on `components/auth/ProtectedRoute.tsx`.

Backend conventions:
- Keep router handlers thin; push logic into services where practical.
- Prefer typed response schemas and explicit error handling.
- Avoid breaking existing endpoints without migration notes.

Safety:
- Never hardcode secrets.
- Avoid destructive data operations unless explicitly requested.
